Reshape Data¶

In [64]:
# Extract # of MI's from string
def get_MI(row):
    if row['Method'] in ['A', 'W']:
            return row['variable'].split('_')[1][2:]
    else:
        return '0'

In [65]:
eff.columns = ['Mmech', 'Trt_Ass', 'Trt_Eff', 'Imputation_Y', 'Complete Data', 'CCA',
       'W_MI5', 'W_MI20', 'W_MI50', 'A_MI5', 'A_MI20', 'A_MI50']
std.columns = ['Mmech', 'Trt_Ass', 'Trt_Eff', 'Imputation_Y', 'Complete Data', 'CCA',
       'W_MI5', 'W_MI20', 'W_MI50', 'A_MI5', 'A_MI20', 'A_MI50']
In [66]:
# Reformat Effect Estimate
eff = pd.melt(eff, id_vars=['Mmech', 'Trt_Ass', 'Trt_Eff', 'Imputation_Y'], value_vars=['Complete Data', 'CCA',
       'W_MI5', 'W_MI20', 'W_MI50', 'A_MI5', 'A_MI20', 'A_MI50'])

eff['Method'] = eff['variable'].apply(lambda x: x.split('_')[0])

eff['MI'] = eff.apply(get_MI, axis=1)

eff['Estimate'] = eff['value']

eff.drop(['variable', 'value'], axis=1, inplace=True)

eff['Bias'] = eff['Estimate'] - 5
In [67]:
# Reformat STD
std = pd.melt(std, id_vars=['Mmech', 'Trt_Ass', 'Trt_Eff', 'Imputation_Y'], value_vars=['Complete Data', 'CCA',
       'W_MI5', 'W_MI20', 'W_MI50', 'A_MI5', 'A_MI20', 'A_MI50'])

std['Method'] = std['variable'].apply(lambda x: x.split('_')[0])

std['MI'] = std.apply(get_MI, axis=1)

std['Estimate'] = std['value']

std.drop(['variable', 'value'], axis=1, inplace=True)

In [68]:
# Dictionary of Parameters
mmech = {0:'MCAR',
         1:'MAR1 - missingness only on control x2',
         2:'missingness on both trt and control x2'}

trt_ass = {0:'Trt Assignment Depends on x1',
           1:'Trt Assignment Depends on x2',
           2:'Trt Assignment Depends on x1, x2',
           3:'Trt Assignment Depends on x1, x2, y'}

trt_eff = {0:'Trt Effect Depends on x1',
           1:'Trt Effect Depends on x2',
           2:'Trt Effect Depends on x1, x2'
          }

imputation_y = {0:'Y NOT in imputation',
               1:'Y in imputation'}

In [70]:
# Effect Estimate
eff2 = eff.loc[eff.Method.isin(['A', 'W', 'CCA'])].reset_index(drop=True)

# Loop Through All Parameters
for j in range(0,4):
        for k in range(0,3):
                temp = eff2.loc[(eff2.Trt_Ass==j) & (eff2.Trt_Eff==k)]
                print(trt_ass[j])
                print(trt_eff[k])
                graph = sns.FacetGrid(temp, row = 'Mmech', col="Imputation_Y", hue='Method')
                graph.map(sns.pointplot, "MI", "Bias", order = None, errorbar=None)
                graph.add_legend()
                graph.map(plt.axhline, y=0, ls='--', c='red')
                plt.show()

# Effect Estimate
std2 = std.loc[std.Method.isin(['A', 'W', 'CCA'])].reset_index(drop=True)

# Loop Through All Parameters
for j in range(0,4):
        for k in range(0,3):
                temp = std2.loc[(std2.Trt_Ass==j) & (std2.Trt_Eff==k)]
                print(trt_ass[j])
                print(trt_eff[k])
                graph = sns.FacetGrid(temp, row = 'Mmech', col="Imputation_Y", hue='Method')
                graph.map(sns.pointplot, "MI", "Estimate", order = None, errorbar=None)
                graph.add_legend()
                graph.map(plt.axhline, y=0, ls='--', c='red')
                plt.show()
